# =============================================================================
# Fantasy MMORPG - Root Environment Configuration
# =============================================================================
# 
# IMPORTANT: This is the ROOT directory .env.example file.
# 
# For the API backend configuration (including Prisma/Database setup),
# please use: packages/api/.env.example
# 
# To set up the database:
# 1. Copy packages/api/.env.example to packages/api/.env
# 2. Start PostgreSQL using Docker: npm run docker:db:start
# 3. Run migrations: npm run prisma:migrate
# 
# For quick setup, run: npm run setup
# 
# Docker Database Commands:
# - npm run docker:db:start   - Start PostgreSQL in Docker
# - npm run docker:db:stop    - Stop the database
# - npm run docker:db:logs    - View database logs
# - npm run docker:db:reset   - Reset database (deletes all data)
# 
# =============================================================================

# This file exists to provide guidance when users try to set up from root directory.
# The actual configuration files are in the respective packages:
# - API Backend: packages/api/.env
# - Frontend: packages/frontend/.env.local (if needed)
# - Game Server: Configuration is in packages/gameserver/ (Go environment)
